data.title: San Diego Multifamily Summit
data.meta_description: Unlock insights at the Bisnow San Diego Multifamily & Residential Conference with speakers from Wakeland Housing, Housing on Merit and Toll Brothers. Dive into strategies for development, financing and community building in San Diego's housing market.
data.text:
Why You Won't Want To Miss This CRE Deal-Making Conference:

What You'll Learn From This Multifamily & Residential Event:

What strategies are being implemented to successfully hold together development and acquisition deals in today's environment?

Building the capital stack has been one of the main challenges in multifamily development in the past year. How are developers and investors creatively constructing their capital stack in today’s challenging environment?

Where in San Diego are developers and investors finding the most opportunity to deploy capital in today’s market?

With rising construction costs, how are contractors, developers and designers developing creative solutions to execute project timelines without impacting their bottom lines?

What incentives exist for developers to encourage affordable housing projects?

What creative financing options exist today and how are developers taking advantage of these?

What architecture and design trends are at the forefront of new multifamily development?

What are owners, developers, property managers and leasing agents doing to help foster community within their buildings?

How are owners incentivizing residents to renew leases in an uncertain market?

Projects To Be Discussed:

Hines - Riverwalk: 5M SF mixed-use master plan in Mission Valley, San Diego. Phase 1: 720 units and 75K SF retail under construction.

MG Properties - Pulse Millenia

KTGY - Winslow (completed: 4Q2023) /// Siena | Stylus (completed March 2021) /// Purl (completed September 2020) /// Vive on Park (opened October 2017) /// College View Apartments (Opening for occupancy Fall 2024) /// Park Avenue Apartments (pending building permit approval; 2Q-3Q24)

MVE Architects - Hillcrest

KPFF - UCSD Pepper Canyon West: Two 22-story residential buildings, each attached to a 6-story ribbon-like structure, over parking to house 1,300 tenants totaling 650,000-sf in La Jolla /// Kindred-BRIDGE Affordable Housing: A new 8-story residential buildings with 130 units totaling 181,399-sf in San Diego /// Merge 56 BLK-03 Affordable Housing: A new 4-story residential building with 47 units totaling 60,000-sf in San Diego /// Kettner Crossing: A new 8-story residential building with 63 units over parking totaling 78,113-sf in San Diego /// 1401 Imperial Avenue – Adaptive Reuse & Affordable Housing: A new 19-story residential building with 176 units totaling 138,891-sf in San Diego /// Town & Country Apartments, San Diego, Ca: Four new 7-story residential buildings with a total of 835 units and parking totaling 1,542,947-sf in San Diego /// “The Helm” Affordable Housing: A new 7-story residential building with 77 units totaling 53,000-sf in San Diego /// Alta Ink: A new 6-story residential building with 162 units over parking totaling 270,575-sf in Los Angeles /// 4th + J Apartments: A new 6-story residential building with 170 units over parking totaling 189,000-sf in San Diego /// “The Link” Affordable Housing: A new 7-story residential building with 88 units totaling 52,830-sf in San Diego /// Cypress Apartments: A new 6-story residential building with 62 units totaling 30,000-sf in San Diego /// Cedar Gateway: Mixed-Use Development A new 7-story residential building with a total of 65 units over parking totaling 132,716-sf in San Diego

GLO Architecture - 64-unit The Howard /// 78-unit The Refuge /// 130-unit Wildomar Ranch /// 80-unit Kifer Senior /// 9-unit Genesis /// 66-units Beaumont Residences

How You'll Do More Business From Attending This Summit: Join industry leaders as they discuss the current multifamily landscape, trends in financing, investing and development as well as construction and design predictions. Learn how industry leaders are working to increase housing supply to build a better and more affordable future in San Diego.

Who You'll Network With At This Discussion: Owners, developers, investors, architects, construction, designers, brokers, leasing agents, lawyers, financial institutions and government officials.

Why You Should Attend This Session: Bisnow events bring together the biggest power players in the industry to identify opportunities, build your network and expand your business. With the largest audience of commercial real estate professionals in the world, no one knows how to help your business more than us.
